properties.Name: ExperianUccFilingsSummary
properties.Description: Companies that extend secured loans to other businesses file Uniform Commercial Code (UCC) documents with the appropriate secretary of state office to protect their interest in the asset. This is a summary of the last 2 years of UCC filing information. It does not show detail, but does show the filing activity.

Columns.Name: ExperianFileNumber
Columns.Description: The unique and persistent number that identifies and tracks the Experian company.

Columns.Name: ProfileTimestamp
Columns.Description: The timestamp of the Experian profile.

Columns.Name: NumberCautionaryUccs
Columns.Description:
The number of cautionary UCC filings.

The presence of cautionary UCC filings indicates that the business has pledged key assets such as accounts, accounts receivable, contracts, hereafter-acquired inventory, leases, notes receivable or proceeds to secure financing.

Cautionary UCC Filing:
A Uniform Commercial Code (UCC) filing where one of the following types of collateral have been pledged:
- Accounts
- Accounts receivable
- Contracts
- Hereafter acquired property
- Inventory
- Leases
- Notes receivable
- Proceeds

Columns.Name: TotalUccFilings
Columns.Description: The total UCC filings for the period.

Columns.Name: NumberOfReleasedTerminatedUccFilings
Columns.Description: The number of released or terminated UCC filings.

Columns.Name: NumberOfContinuousUccFilings
Columns.Description: The number of continuous UCC filings.

Columns.Name: NumberOfAmendedAssignedUccFilings
Columns.Description:
The number of assigned or amended UCC filings.

Assignment - This is an assignment of interest to another secured party. Sometimes this is used to assign certain portions of collateral to specific secured parties.

Amendment (Party Information) - the change of a UCC filing name or address
